<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,551,671,697]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1912" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1912" box="[238,551,671,697]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Houardiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,385,671,697]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Houardiella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer" box="[392,551,671,697]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1912) pp. 66 - 67, 69 - 72, 74 - 79, 107 - 108, 126 - 128, In: Houard, C. Les zoocecidies du nord de l'Afrique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France. 81, 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1912">
Kieffer, 
<number box="[493,551,671,697]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,746,972]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[151,293,746,771]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Houardiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,293,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Houardiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises two described species in the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[828,996,746,772]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Asphondyliini">Asphondyliini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gagne" box="[1012,1162,746,772]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Gagne, R. J. (2004) A Catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington 25, 1 - 408." type="journal article" year="2004">
Gagné 
<number box="[1098,1162,746,772]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is closely related to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[269,416,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Asphondylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,416,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Asphondylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with its needle-like, piercing ovipositor that is accompanied by a pair of basal lobes at its base, and the progressively shorter flagellomeres in the female. It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1259,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Asphondylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1112,1259,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Asphondylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having onesegmented (as opposed to three-segmented) palpi, a single tooth rather than two teeth on the male gonostylus, and an apical, posterior extension of the gonocoxite. Immature stages resemble those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1367,906,931]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Asphondylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1367,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Asphondylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with well developed cephalic horns and abdominal spines in pupae, and a massive spatula in larvae.
</paragraph>
